// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/lXsfWH tatami tiling spiral vortex anim, 2024 by jt
// based on https://www.shadertoy.com/view/43XBWn tatami tiling spiral
// related pattern: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/clGcDd simple tatami square

// A square tiled with tatamis with ids 0,1,2,3... spiralling outwards:
// dominos / "dimers" in a spiral around a central monomino / "monomer"
// Animated to verify ids (but mostly just for fun).

// The underlying spiral is basically a https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulam_spiral
// with index right-shifted by one to join adjacent monominos to dominos.
// (Depending on an additional offset spiral starts with monomino or domino.)

// If I understand correctly the combination of 1x1 and 2x1 ("monomer"/"monomino"? and "dimer"/"domino") is (sometimes?) called Tatami-tiling.
// Some articles about tatami-tilings:
// https://www.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/~kyodo/kokyuroku/contents/pdf/1691-01.pdf
// https://arxiv.org/pdf/1103.3309
// https://www.emis.de/journals/EJC/Volume_18/PDF/v18i1p109.pdf
// https://webhome.cs.uvic.ca/~ruskey/Publications/Tatami/TatamiDraftSubmitted.pdf
// https://mathoverflow.net/questions/103165/monomer-dimer-tatami-tilings-need-better-relationships-with-other-math-summary
// Possibly also in: Knuth, The Art of Computer Programming, Volume 4A Combinatorial Algorithms, Part 1
// (and in general some tiling articles can be found in https://www.combinatorics.org/ )

// tags: spiral, square, tiling, vortex, anim, ulam, tatami, domino, dimer, 2x1, monomer, monomino, 1x1, 1x2

